### CouchDB Revision Control Demo (_rev)
@base = http://admin:admin@localhost:5984
@db = demo_multi_shape
@docId = rev_demo_001
@currentRev = 1-placeholder
@latestRev = 1-placeholder

### 1) Create/replace demo document (new _rev)
PUT {{base}}/{{db}}/{{docId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "rev_demo",
  "step": 1,
  "message": "initial write"
}

### 2) Read current document and copy _rev as currentRev
GET {{base}}/{{db}}/{{docId}}

### 3) Update using currentRev (expected: success)
# Replace {{currentRev}} with _rev from step 2.
PUT {{base}}/{{db}}/{{docId}}?rev={{currentRev}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "rev_demo",
  "step": 2,
  "message": "update with current _rev"
}

### 4) Reuse stale currentRev again (expected: 409 conflict)
PUT {{base}}/{{db}}/{{docId}}?rev={{currentRev}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "rev_demo",
  "step": 3,
  "message": "stale write should conflict"
}

### 5) Read latest document and copy _rev as latestRev
GET {{base}}/{{db}}/{{docId}}

### 6) All Version
GET {{base}}/{{db}}/{{docId}}?revs=true



